    {
      "name": "daily-training-plan",
      "description": "Strength-focused daily training plan at 5:30 AM PT based on Strava data, muscle group rotation, and weather",
      "enabled": true,
      "schedule": {
        "type": "cron",
        "expression": "30 5 * * *",
        "tz": "America/Los_Angeles"
      },
      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "message": "Generate Alex's daily training plan with a STRENGTH TRAINING focus. Steps:\n1. Use the strava skill to fetch the last 14 days of activities (per_page=50) — analyze training load, rest days, intensity patterns, and recent volume.\n2. Check today's weather for Mountain View/Palo Alto.\n3. Based on the data, generate a personalized training recommendation for TODAY. PRIORITIZE STRENGTH TRAINING:\n   - Primary workout: Strength session with specific exercises, sets, reps, and target muscle groups. Follow a PPL (Push/Pull/Legs) or Upper/Lower split rotation based on what was trained recently.\n   - Include compound lifts as the foundation (squat, deadlift, bench, OHP, rows, pull-ups)\n   - Add accessory work (3-4 exercises)\n   - Specify warm-up sets and working set weights if prior data available\n   - Optional: secondary cardio suggestion (short ride, zone 2 recovery spin) only if training load allows\n   - Rest day recommendation ONLY if recent load demands it — even then suggest mobility/light lifting\n   - Weather considerations only for optional outdoor cardio\n   - Brief rationale based on recent training load and muscle group rotation\n4. Keep it concise and motivating. Use emojis. Format for Discord.\n5. IMPORTANT: Keep each message under 1900 characters — split across multiple send_message calls if needed.\n6. Send the plan to channel 1491834183889457285 (#disclaw-training)."
      },
      "delivery": {
