    {
      "name": "daily-food-thread",
      "description": "Daily food tracking thread at 5 AM PT with Strava-adjusted calorie targets",
      "enabled": true,
      "schedule": {
        "type": "cron",
        "expression": "0 5 * * *",
        "tz": "America/Los_Angeles"
      },
      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "message": "Create a daily food tracking thread for Alex. Steps:\n1. Read memory file data/memory/food_log.md for current stats and targets.\n2. Use the strava skill to fetch today's activities and grab exercise calories.\n3. Calculate adjusted calorie budget: 1700 BMR + (Strava exercise calories × 0.6 eat-back). If no exercise yet, use base 1700.\n4. Calculate adjusted macros: Protein 140-155g (priority), Fat 50-60g, Carbs fill remaining calories.\n5. Create a new thread in channel 1492254579629359114 named with today's date (e.g. \"4/11\").\n6. Post an opening message in the thread with:\n   - Today's adjusted calorie budget and macro targets\n   - Any Strava exercise already logged and calories burned\n   - A reminder to post meals (text or photo) for tracking\n   - Keep it concise, use emojis\n7. IMPORTANT: Keep each message under 1900 characters."
      },
